.\" termin.al-name: cat
.\" termin.al-usage: cat <path> [path ...]
.\" termin.al-summary: Print raw virtual document content.
.TH CAT 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
cat \- Print raw virtual document content.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
cat <path> [path ...]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reads one or more files from termin.al's virtual filesystem and writes their raw document text to the current terminal scrollback. Paths are resolved relative to the current pane directory; absolute virtual paths begin with
.BR ~ .
Files are read in argument order without Markdown rendering, headings or separators.
.SH OUTPUT
Each successful operand creates one text output in the same order as its argument. An empty document produces an empty text output.
.SH FAILURES
One to 32 paths are required. Options before
.B --
are unsupported. Invalid, missing, directory, locked or unavailable operands reject the command. If any read fails or cancellation occurs, no accumulated partial output is returned.
.SH LIMITS
At most 32 file operands are accepted per invocation.
.SH NOTES
The virtual corpus is read-only; cat never reads the browser host or local machine filesystem.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ cat about.md
$ cat ~/skills.md ~/tools.md
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
head(1), tail(1), less(1), pwd(1)
